    "message_1": "A math student needs to find the value of 'y' for a given 'x' using interpolation method with the help of following data points:\n\n|x|1|2|3|4|\n|--|-|-|-|-|\n|y|3|2|1|4|\n\nUsing the Lagrange polynomial method, what is the value of 'y' when 'x' is equal to 2.5?",
    "message_2": "To find the value of 'y' when 'x' is equal to 2.5 using the Lagrange polynomial method, we need to use the following formula:\n\nL(x) = L0(x) * y0 + L1(x) * y1 + L2(x) * y2 + L3(x) * y3\n\nwhere Lk(x) is the k-th Lagrange basis polynomial and yk is the corresponding y-value.\n\nFor the given data points:\n\nx0 = 1, y0 = 3\nx1 = 2, y1 = 2\nx2 = 3, y2 = 1\nx3 = 4, y3 = 4\n\nNow, we need to find the Lagrange basis polynomials L0(x), L1(x), L2(x), and L3(x):\n\nL0(x) = ((x - x1)(x - x2)(x - x3))/((x0 - x1)(x0 - x2)(x0 - x3))\nL1(x) = ((x - x0)(x - x2)(x - x3))/((x1 - x0)(x1 - x2)(x1 - x3))\nL2(x) = ((x - x0)(x - x1)(x - x3))/((x2 - x0)(x2 - x1)(x2 - x3))\nL3(x) = ((x - x0)(x - x1)(x - x2))/((x3 - x0)(x3 - x1)(x3 - x2))\n\nNow, we need to find the value of L(x) when x = 2.5:\n\nL0(2.5) = ((2.5 - 2)(2.5 - 3)(2.5 - 4))/((1 - 2)(1 - 3)(1 - 4)) = (0.5 * (-0.5) * (-1.5))/((-1)(-2)(-3)) = 0.25\nL1(2.5) = ((2.5 - 1)(2.5 - 3)(2.5 - 4))/((2 - 1)(2 - 3)(2 - 4)) = (1.5 * (-0.5) * (-1.5))/((1)(-1)(-2)) = -1.125\nL2(2.5) = ((2.5 - 1)(2.5 - 2)(2.5 - 4))/((3 - 1)(3 - 2)(3 - 4)) = (1.5 * 0.5 * (-1.5))/((2)(1)(-1)) = 0.75\nL3(2.5) = ((2.5 - 1)(2.5 - 2)(2.5 - 3))/((4 - 1)(4 - 2)(4 - 3)) = (1.5 * 0.5 * 0.5)/((3)(2)(1)) = 0.125\n\nNow, we can find the value of y when x = 2.5:\n\ny(2.5) = L0(2.5) * y0 + L1(2.5) * y1 + L2(2.5) * y2 + L3(2.5) * y3\ny(2.5) = 0.25 * 3 + (-1.125) * 2 + 0.75 * 1 + 0.125 * 4\ny(2.5) = 0.75 - 2.25 + 0.75 + 0.5\ny(2.5) = 0.75\n\nSo, the value of 'y' when 'x' is equal to 2.5 is 0.75."
